<h4><a name="cat1-q1"></a>How does the Penny Pledge work?</h4>
<p>The penny pledge is a social match of one penny per donor. When you make a penny pledge for a specific campaign, you
  select the penny pledge and you also select a maximum donation amount. Your final donation amount will be determined
  as follows: the total number of unique donors at the end of the campaign multiplied by one penny for each donor. For
  example, if there are 5,000 donors at the end of a campaign, your donation amount will be 5,000 pennies ($50.00). If
  the total number of donors exceeds your maximum pledge amount, your final donation will be the maximum pledge amount.
  For example, if you selected a $10 maximum and 5,000 people donate, your donation will remain at the $10 limit you
  selected.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q2"></a>What is a fixed donation?</h4>
<p>A fixed donation is just that, a specific fixed amount that a donor wishes to give. The amount a donor is charged for
  a fixed donation is the exact amount of the fixed donation. This donation option is for donors who wish to donate a
  specific amount. Donors who make fixed donations are still part of the social match and counted in the total number of
  donors used to calculate the final penny pledge donation amounts.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q3"></a>Is my donation tax deductible?</h4>
<p>You should consult with your tax advisor on all contributions you make. Many organizations who use the Kiindly
  service are non profit organizations. We will provide you with a receipt for each donation you make that you may use
  for your tax records should the donation qualify as tax deductible.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q4"></a>Am I charged 1 penny at a time?</h4>
<p>No, we process all donations at the end of the campaign. When you first enter your credit card, we do validate the
  card but we don't process your final contribution until the end of the campaign.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q5"></a>When do I get charged?</h4>
<p>Within 7 days after the end of the campaign, we will process your credit card and send you a receipt. Once you
  complete your pledge or fixed donation you will receive a confirmation email which contains the end date of the
  campaign.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q6"></a>Is my donation matched?</h4>
<p>The virtue of the Kiindly Penny Pledge is the social match. Anyone who takes the penny pledge is agreeing to pay one
  penny multiplied by the total number of donors in the campaign, including donors who make fixed pledges. As a result,
  when you make a fixed or penny pledge, dozens, hundreds, or thousands of other donors increase their pledge by
  $.01.<br/>
  In addition, an individual campaign may have a corporate match in effect. If this is the case, it will be indicated in
  the 'About this campaign' text on the campaign landing page.</p>

<h4><a name="cat1-q7"></a>Can I make multiple donations to increase the amount per donor?</h4>
<p>No. While this is a creative idea, it does not match the spirit of the social match provided by Kiindly. As a result,
  we only count donors as unique donors which means if you make multiple donations, you will be charged for all of your
  donations, but you will only be counted once in calculating the number of donors for the penny pledge calculation.</p>


