<h4><a name="cat3-q1"></a>How much of my donation goes to this campaign?</h4>
<p>The organization running the campaign will receive the sum of all donations minus the actual credit card fee charged
  by the credit card provider and minus the transaction fee charged by Kiindly. Since all donations taken via a credit
  card include a credit card fee, the only incremental charge for the organization is the Kiindly transaction fee. The
  final amount the organization receives is the sum of all donations net of the credit card fees minus $1.20 multiplied
  by the number of donors (Kiindly's transaction fee).</p>

<h4><a name="cat3-q2"></a>Why is there a transaction fee?</h4>
<p>Fundraising often requires organizations to spend significant amounts of money with third party experts,
  telemarketers, and direct mail in order to accomplish fundraising goals. A typical fundraising campaign not run
  through Kiindly will often cost 15-20% of the total amount raised, meaning only 80-85% of your donation will go to the
  organization and the organization must often take the risk of the marketing investment regardless of the success of
  the campaign. Through Kiindly, organizations take on zero risk in the marketing investment (there are no upfront
  costs) and the final cost is often significantly less than the cost of traditional means of fundraising. Our goal at
  Kiindly is to cover our costs and make a fair profit so that we can help many more organizations. We charge a
  transaction fee that we believe is fair and on par with transaction fees charged for other types of online purchases
  such as movies and events.</p>


